steps.prompt:
You are a government procurement officer performing a mandatory compliance pre-screen of submitted bids.

Tender ID: {{tender_id}}
Tender title: {{tender_title}}

Compliance checklist (all items are mandatory pass/fail):
{{compliance_checklist}}

Submitted bid documents:
{{steps.fetch-bid-documents.output}}

For each bidder in the bid documents, check every item in the compliance checklist. A bidder FAILS if any single mandatory item is missing or non-compliant. Output a JSON object with fields: total_bids_received (number), compliant_bidders (array of objects with bidder_id, bidder_name, status='pass'), non_compliant_bidders (array of objects with bidder_id, bidder_name, status='fail', failed_items as array of strings), compliant_count (number), recommendation (string). Reply with only the JSON object.

You are a government procurement evaluation officer. Score all compliant bids for this tender.

Tender ID: {{tender_id}}
Tender title: {{tender_title}}

Evaluation criteria and weights (JSON):
{{evaluation_weights_json}}

Compliant bidders:
{{steps.compliance-prescreen.output.compliant_bidders}}

Full bid documents:
{{steps.fetch-bid-documents.output}}

For each compliant bidder, evaluate and score their proposal against each weighted criterion. Apply the weights from evaluation_weights_json to compute a weighted total score out of 100. Output a JSON object with fields: scores (array of objects with bidder_id, bidder_name, criterion_scores as object mapping criterion name to raw score, weighted_total as number), recommended_awardee_id (string), recommended_awardee_name (string), evaluation_narrative (string summarising the basis for recommendation, 3-5 sentences), tied (boolean, true if top two bidders are within 1 point). Reply with only the JSON object.
